<!-- HERITAGE OVERHAUL: the Angre naval line (wave 3). Completes Bharat's
     naval identity across the Modern melee-naval branch: Angre Galbat (T1,
     replaces Ironclad) -> Angre Ghurab (T2, replaces Cruiser) -> Azad Hind
     Nau Sena (T3, replaces Destroyer — already shipped in bharat-units-2.xml).
     Official multi-tier Modern naval-unique precedent: Meiji's Mikasa
     (UNIT_MIKASA/UNIT_MIKASA_2 replacing Dreadnought/Battleship,
     age-modern/data/units.xml:529-530).

     HISTORICAL KERNEL (Tier A, 2026-07-18 research): Sarkhel Kanhoji Angre's
     Maratha navy (c. 1698-1729) controlled the Konkan coast with fast
     gallivats (galbat) and gun-ghurabs, forcing European powers to buy
     sea-passes — documented in East India Company records and B.K. Apte's
     history of the Maratha navy. Base-game Chola already carries the medieval
     naval story (3-tier Kalam line + Ottru commander) on this leader's
     Maurya->Chola->Bharat path; this line is its early-colonial-era
     continuation. Framing: pre-independence Indian naval tradition, civ-side
     heritage — no Axis content.

     Stats mirror the replaced base units exactly (Ironclad 45/20/20 r1 cost
     280 maint 6; Cruiser 50/25/25 r1 cost 340 maint 9 — age-modern/data/
     units.xml:173,180,289,296,368,375), + the home-waters ability shared with
     Nau Sena's identity ("Sarkhel's Coast", +3 CS in friendly territory) at
     the proven Cossack-pattern requirement set. No UnitUpgrades rows — same
     as bharat-units-2.xml, replacements ride the base upgrade chain
     (Ironclad->Cruiser->Destroyer). Unit flags: placeholder = nau_sena flag
     until Grok art lands (IMAGINE-PROMPTS #16). -->
